This paper deals with joint source channel coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves communication over a multiple access channel (MAC), which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses coding techniques, which can be related to network information theory (cs.NI) and coding theory (cs.CC).
